<item>
            <title>[HBASE-12168] Document Rest gateway SPNEGO-based authentication for client</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-12168</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;After &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-5050&quot; title=&quot;[rest] SPNEGO-based authentication&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-5050&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-5050&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, we seem to support SPNEGO-based authentication from client on Rest gateway. But I had a tough time finding the info.&lt;br/&gt;
The support is not mentioned in Security book. In the security book, we still have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;It should be possible for clients to authenticate with the HBase cluster through the REST gateway in a pass-through manner via SPEGNO HTTP authentication. This is future work.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The release note in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-5050&quot; title=&quot;[rest] SPNEGO-based authentication&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-5050&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-5050&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; seems to be obsolete as well. e.g.&lt;br/&gt;
hbase.rest.kerberos.spnego.principal seems to be obsolete.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
